		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">leonk wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Actually, the ciclone chip which I believe all this hardware has goes against the digital millennium act (since it's reverse engineering of copyright material) and hence selling it in the USA is technically illegal.</div>
<br />O RLY? See <em>Chamberlain v. Skylink</em> and <em>Lexmark v. Static Control</em>, which have limited the scope of the DMCA with respect to access control methods used as a generic lock-in mechanism rather than around specific copyrighted works.

		

